<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880505-0117 </DOCNO><HL> Who's News: Mellon Names J.B. Stewart To Corporate-Finance Post </HL><SO> </SO><CO> MEL WNEWS </CO><DATELINE> PITTSBURGH  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Mellon Bank Corp. named Jamie B. Stewart Jr. executive vice president in the company's Corporate Finance Group. Mr. Stewart, 43 years old, will be responsible for expanding Mellon's investment-banking and corporate-finance capabilities. In the newly created position, Mr. Stewart also will assume responsibility for Mellon Bank Canada and will head Mellon's Hong Kong, Tokyo, London and Australian operations.    Prior to joining Mellon, Mr. Stewart was senior vice president and director of Bank of America's Investment Banking Group, where he was responsible for the bank's U.S. investment-banking activities and was chairman of the bank's three venture-capital subsidiaries. Bank of America is a unit of San Francisco-based Bank America Corp. </TEXT></DOC>